8:
Damn it all! How could I let this
happen?
11:
This is bad, real bad! I can't believe I
let my guard down!
25:
Sorry, beardie, but Celtie gets what
she wants! Since I gave ya those
ninja tools, maybe let it slide?
30:
You underhanded weasels, teamin'
up and attacking me in my sleep! If
there are more of ya, come out now!
34:
This can't be the work of a single
ninja! Someone else is behind this!
43:
Alk... Why would you get involved in
this?
49:
There have been a number of
complaints about unpaid bar tabs...
52:
Mr. Takamori told me through a
forced smile that he had to
reimburse some of the owners...
55:
We don't allow things like that
around here.
59:
Whoa whoa whoa, I getcha! I'll pay
for everything, just never make that
face again!
62:
But I won't spar with that girl from
Tris... I absolutely refuse!
67:
Oh come on, what's the harm in it?
Seems like it'd be a great match!
71:
Look... I'm a pretty ordinary sword
fighter. I'm just good at getting a few
hits in first.
74: But that's it! After that, I just... just...
86:
Ya try to force an old body to move
when it just won't... What do you get
from all that?
90:
NOTHING! 'Cept the feeling of all
those years on your bones. You can't
understand that since you're still
growing!
97:
But... about those first few hits... How
would you get them?
101:
That part's obvious! Alk, my boy, you
need to get friendly with a few
ladies...
109:
Hooooold on! It was a joke, just an
old man making a joke, sorry!
113:
Grrrrr. Fine, ya already caught me,
so I might as well do the thing...
124:
Ya gotta be kiddin' me... What's with
all the commotion?
129:
Simple. When people heard they
could train with or battle Vyron, the
shadowy powerhouse, they all
wanted to join in.
140:
The last match will be a sparring
session with Celtie, but I have five
other matches prepared.
142:
First, a test of strength. Then speed
followed by accuracy...
146:
How much are you gonna make this
old man work?
149:
The fourth match is a drinking
competition...
153:
Selgir, was that your suggestion?!
Are you out of your mind?!
158:
Let's get started with the first match,
then.
161:
Now, for the moment you've all been
waiting for!
164:
It is I, Toria, here to represent the
grand kingdom of Mirea! You'll be
facing me in a sumo match!
168:
Is this some kinda joke? 
...Okay, I get what's going on.
171:
Geez... Drag the old man out just to
play silly pranks on him, that it?
174:
Sorry for putting ya through the
hassle, princess. At least you're the
perfect type for me to wrestle—
185:
The five matches have begun.
Things are about to heat up.
192:
Hmph, so the fourth match comes
to an end. The fifth should be quite
the sight.
204:
Wait, we obviously can't do it like
this! How are you still standing,
Selgir?!
209:
We can certainly continue—the guy
can use detox magic, after all.
214:
And yet you're always talking about
how you can handle your liquor.
Show no mercy, Shirley!
219:
Understood... Now, Sir Vyron, it's time
for our duel!
223:
...You really like runnin' an old man
through the wringer, huh?
227:
A friend once taught me not to use
age as an excuse to avoid a chance
to improve. You can still fight, Vyron.
266: Hah! For all that old man's whining...
275:
Hm, so he does. It's good to enjoy
oneself from time to time.
278:
Honestly, he seems better than
usual when being tossed around by
you all.
285: What a pain in the ass...
